The paper proposes a visual analytics tool for pattern searching in trendlines, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and database (DB) aspects. The system uses natural language processing (NLP) and regular expressions (regex), which are related to information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also mentions the use of perceptually-aware scoring methodologies, which are relevant to computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.HC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
